  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h3>We provide all students with the opportunity to participate in a comprehensive training schedule designed to improve all attributes of your game.</h3>
<p>With the chance to compete in the highest level national and regional competitions our detailed, positional-specific, training programme will enable you to develop your technical, tactical, mental and physical attributes.</p>
<h4>Why be part of our Rugby Academy?</h4>
<ul>
<li>Specialist position-specific coaching - a key strength of the programme</li>
<li>Top facilities and equipment</li>
<li>Five days per week training programme (three rugby sessions and two gym sessions)</li>
<li>Pre-season training sessions</li>
<li>Weekly fixtures (normally on Wednesday)</li>
<li>Opportunity to play in national and regional competitions, testing yourself against the best schools and colleges in England (including Essex Cup, Daily Mail Trophy, NatWest Schools Cup &amp; Vase, Elite League, Elite Cup and Regional 10s tournament)</li>
<li>Access to a first-class physiotherapist</li>
<li>Access to a strength and conditioning specialist</li>
<li>Guest coaches who have played at a high level.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Your training programme will include:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Individual strength and conditioning programme</li>
<li>Speed and power</li>
<li>Reaction time</li>
<li>Contact skills</li>
<li>Decision-making</li>
<li>Ball-handling</li>
<li>Position specific training</li>
<li>Team cohesion.</li>
</ul>
<h4>The Coaching Team </h4>
<p>Our coaching team is made up of three team coaches, a Strength &amp; Conditioning Coach and a Sports Rehabilitator. Each member of the team will play a vital role in your development as a player both on and off the field.</p>
<p>All coaches have valuable experience and many of them still work or compete within the sporting industry.  </p>
<p> </p>]]></mainContent>
